The paper deals with interactive coding schemes that are resilient to erasures in a distributed computation setting. This involves concepts from information theory (cs.IT), cryptography (cs.CR), distributed computing (cs.DC), coding theory (cs.CC), and data structures (cs.DS). Therefore, these are the most likely sub-categories that this paper belongs to, ordered from most to least likely.
